{
  "id": "c0c0c0c0-0097-0000-0000-000000000000",
  "name": "Gap Analysis: Philosophy vs. Reality",
  "type": "871ae771-b9b1-4f40-8c7f-d9038bfb69c3",
  "created": 1742198400000,
  "modified": 1773826168439,
  "content": {
    "description": [
      ":doc",
      [
        ":p",
        [
          ":em",
          {
            "s": "March 2026 — A review of the system's philosophical foundations vs. current capabilities."
          }
        ]
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Cross-reference: "
        },
        [
          ":item-ref",
          "c0c0c0c0-0090-0000-0000-000000000000"
        ],
        {
          "s": " covers prioritized next steps. "
        },
        [
          ":item-ref",
          "c0c0c0c0-0042-0000-0000-000000000000"
        ],
        {
          "s": " catalogs the full possibility space. This item asks a different question: "
        },
        [
          ":strong",
          {
            "s": "where does the system fall short of its own stated philosophy?"
          }
        ]
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "The review measures Hobson against its five inspirations ("
        },
        [
          ":item-ref",
          "a0a0a0a0-d0c0-4000-8000-000000000001"
        ],
        {
          "s": "): Conway's Humane Dozen, Smalltalk's image persistence, Lisp's REPL-first development, Obenauer's itemized OS, and Obsidian-style linking."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":hr"
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "1. The Trust Gap"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        [
          ":strong",
          {
            "s": "Philosophy violated:"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " Conway's "
        },
        [
          ":em",
          {
            "s": "Robust"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " (actions are reversible, system doesn't break), Smalltalk's "
        },
        [
          ":em",
          {
            "s": "image persistence"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " (everything persists reliably)."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "For Hobson to be a primary information manager, you need to trust it won't lose your data. The current story is thin:"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":ul",
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "IndexedDB is the runtime store."
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " A browser data clear or corrupted IDB wipes the runtime data. The git export workflow to src/items/*.json provides a version-controlled backup, but requires manual export."
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "No undo at the system level."
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " Deleting an item, removing an attachment, changing a type — all irreversible. The Active Text editor now has structural undo/redo, but the system as a whole has no undo concept."
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "Version History is unimplemented."
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " "
            },
            [
              ":item-ref",
              "c0c0c0c0-0043-0000-0000-000000000000"
            ],
            {
              "s": " describes the concept but is marked low priority. For a daily-driver workspace, the inability to see what changed or revert is a serious gap."
            }
          ]
        ]
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        [
          ":strong",
          {
            "s": "Suggested action:"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " The git export workflow is an adequate backup for single-user use. The remaining trust gaps are system-level undo (no way to revert item deletion or type changes) and version history (no way to see what changed). Browser limitations (no filesystem write access in Firefox) make automatic backup to the git directory impractical without external tooling."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":hr"
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "2. The Discoverability Problem"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        [
          ":strong",
          {
            "s": "Philosophy violated:"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " Conway's "
        },
        [
          ":em",
          {
            "s": "Self-Revealing"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " (interface presents choices), "
        },
        [
          ":em",
          {
            "s": "Interactive"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " (each action suggests the next)."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "The "
        },
        [
          ":item-ref",
          "c0c0c0c0-0093-0000-0000-000000000000"
        ],
        {
          "s": " doc already identifies the \"seven conceptual hops\" problem. But the discoverability gap extends beyond understanding the system to finding your own data:"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":ul",
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "Search lacks quality features."
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " The "
            },
            [
              ":item-ref",
              "f1111111-0005-0000-0000-000000000000"
            ],
            {
              "s": " searches names, types, tags, and content bodies — basic content search works. But there is no fuzzy matching, word stemming, or relevance ranking. As item count grows, exact-match search over flat results becomes increasingly inadequate."
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "Spatial canvases need scaling affordances."
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " No snap-to-grid, no alignment guides, no grouping/stacking, no minimap. The spatial metaphor becomes chaotic as workspace size grows."
            }
          ]
        ]
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        [
          ":strong",
          {
            "s": "Suggested action:"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " Search quality improvements — fuzzy matching, stemming, relevance ranking — would be the highest-leverage discoverability feature. Buildable as a userland library item, which would itself demonstrate the system's extensibility."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":hr"
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "3. The Two-Language Problem"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        [
          ":strong",
          {
            "s": "Philosophy violated:"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " Conway's "
        },
        [
          ":em",
          {
            "s": "Unified"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " (source and runtime are the same), "
        },
        [
          ":em",
          {
            "s": "Symmetrical"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " (tool and application are peers). "
        },
        [
          ":item-ref",
          "c0c0c0c0-0093-0000-0000-000000000000"
        ],
        {
          "s": "'s demand for conceptual uniformity."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "The "
        },
        [
          ":item-ref",
          "c0c0c0c0-0058-0000-0000-000000000000"
        ],
        {
          "s": " says Hob should be \"the obvious choice.\" But the infrastructure still privileges JS:"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":ul",
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "All foundational libraries are JS."
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "viewport-rendering"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": ", "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "context-menu-lib"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": ", "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "item-search-lib"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": ", "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "generic-view"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " — the infrastructure that makes everything work is opaque to Hob. Understanding the system still requires reading JS."
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "24 of 48 views are Hob."
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " Good progress, but the remaining 24 include critical views ("
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "type-workshop-view"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " at 750 lines, "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "app-page-view"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " at 374 lines, "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "test-suite-view"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " at 295 lines). The conversion pace vs. the \"obvious choice\" aspiration creates a long tail."
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "The evaluateHob childEnv bug."
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " Per the "
            },
            [
              ":item-ref",
              "c0c0c0c0-005c-0000-0000-000000000000"
            ],
            {
              "s": ", the environment parameter passed to "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "evaluateHob"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " is silently ignored. Code that looks correct but does nothing is a trust problem for anyone reading the system."
            }
          ]
        ]
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        [
          ":strong",
          {
            "s": "Suggested action:"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " Fix the "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "evaluateHob"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " childEnv bug — it undermines the \"transparent\" philosophy when internal machinery silently ignores its inputs."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":hr"
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "4. Active Text Editor Completion"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        [
          ":strong",
          {
            "s": "Philosophy violated:"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " Conway's "
        },
        [
          ":em",
          {
            "s": "Robust"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " and "
        },
        [
          ":em",
          {
            "s": "Continuous"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": "."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "The "
        },
        [
          ":item-ref",
          "c0c0c0c0-0090-0000-0000-000000000000"
        ],
        {
          "s": " correctly identifies this as Priority 1. The remaining gaps (copy/paste, multi-block selection, block reordering) are all things users hit within minutes of sustained writing:"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":ul",
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "Paste from external sources"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " matters more than internal copy/paste. If you can't paste text from a web page or another app, Hobson can't be a primary note-taking tool."
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "Block reordering via keyboard"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " (Alt+Up/Down) would be more natural than drag-and-drop for a keyboard-centric system."
            }
          ]
        ]
      ],
      [
        ":hr"
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "5. Content Gaps for a PIM"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        [
          ":strong",
          {
            "s": "Practical gaps,"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " not philosophy violations. The system handles its chosen domain (text, code, structured data) well. These are feature gaps that limit daily use as a PIM:"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":ul",
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "No images or media."
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " A personal information manager that can't store screenshots, diagrams, or file attachments is fundamentally limited. IndexedDB can store blobs. Even just pasting images into notes (stored as base64 or blob references) would be transformative."
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "No import from standard formats."
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " Markdown files, CSV, bookmarks, OPML — bringing data into Hobson requires writing import scripts. The "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "markdown-to-active-text"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " library exists, but there's no UI for file import."
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "No dates or reminders."
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " "
            },
            [
              ":item-ref",
              "c0c0c0c0-0048-0000-0000-000000000000"
            ],
            {
              "s": " is \"not started.\" For task management and personal organization, the inability to associate dates with items (due dates, reminders, scheduled reviews) is a gap. The task tag exists but there's no date field convention."
            }
          ]
        ]
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        [
          ":strong",
          {
            "s": "Suggested action:"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " Image support in Active Text (paste to blob, "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": ":img"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " AST node) and a drag-and-drop file import UI would open the door to Hobson as a real daily-use PIM."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":hr"
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "6. Architectural Concerns"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "These aren't philosophy violations yet, but are load-bearing assumptions that could fail at scale:"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":ul",
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "Performance at scale."
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " 337 items currently. What happens at 3,000? The "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "query"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " API presumably does full scans of IndexedDB. The spatial canvas renders all attached items simultaneously. The Active Text editor walks entire ASTs. None of these have documented scaling strategies."
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "Module cache invalidation: resolved."
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " Per-item invalidation replaces global clearCache() on save. viewport-manager uses a lazy singleton to reconstruct after re-evaluation. Sticky events enable generic late-activation for watcher items (replaces hardcoded boot-complete replay). Module cleanup lifecycle calls cleanup() on old modules before cache invalidation, removing stale side effects."
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "No PWA / service worker."
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " Conway's \"Always On\" attribute is only partially achieved — the system requires an open browser tab. A service worker could enable offline caching of the bootloader, installability as a desktop app, and (eventually) background processing for reminders or sync."
            }
          ]
        ]
      ],
      [
        ":hr"
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "7. What the Roadmap Gets Right"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "The existing "
        },
        [
          ":item-ref",
          "c0c0c0c0-0090-0000-0000-000000000000"
        ],
        {
          "s": " priorities are well-chosen:"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":ul",
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            {
              "s": "Active Text parity is correctly Priority 1 (it's the daily-use blocker)"
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            {
              "s": "Doc query helpers (Priority 2) address real verbosity in eval blocks"
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            {
              "s": "Hob view conversions (Priority 3) move toward conceptual uniformity"
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            {
              "s": "Hob correctness & stdlib (Priority 4) fixes real bugs"
            }
          ]
        ]
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "The gaps identified here are largely orthogonal — they represent things the roadmap doesn't cover, not disagreements with what it does cover."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":hr"
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "Prioritized Suggestions (Beyond the Roadmap)"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Ranked by impact on the \"can I use Hobson as my primary workspace\" question:"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":ol",
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "System-level undo"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " — deleting an item, removing an attachment, changing a type are all irreversible. The Active Text editor now has structural undo/redo, but the system as a whole has no undo concept. Even a simple \"soft delete\" (archive instead of destroy) or a per-item change log would reduce the cost of mistakes."
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "Search quality"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " — basic content search works, but fuzzy matching, stemming, and relevance ranking would improve discoverability as the item count grows. Buildable as a userland library item."
            }
          ]
        ]
      ]
    ],
    "tags": [
      "bff75873-edb8-412e-81c9-c744e68fe29f"
    ]
  },
  "attachments": []
}